<figure><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/j_rk7NPfdIA5KBKfJS0oBsaIaV2hX4bkguJHv_wVSIA=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9hbXJ5LW5hdnktYnJhbmQtaGVhZGVyLTEuanBn" alt="The Army and Navy Style Guides" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/gggixTIva_8gdSfQqR5lxhdViHZMgNUyG-39jyIfYFQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93NjAwLzIwMjMvMTAvYW1yeS1uYXZ5LWJyYW5kLWhlYWRlci0xLmpwZw== 600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ZKRuNiG-Mp6Tfxn4JfavD1a3jw5ZRS1vTPXDMfgKat0=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MTAwMC8yMDIzLzEwL2FtcnktbmF2eS1icmFuZC1oZWFkZXItMS5qcGc= 1000w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/kZAqnWgJv3CQRFS9uc8Hatqk4-0f0ViiMTsg0qYtTIQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MTYwMC8yMDIzLzEwL2FtcnktbmF2eS1icmFuZC1oZWFkZXItMS5qcGc= 1600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/j_rk7NPfdIA5KBKfJS0oBsaIaV2hX4bkguJHv_wVSIA=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9hbXJ5LW5hdnktYnJhbmQtaGVhZGVyLTEuanBn 2000w" loading="lazy"/></figure><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/fEerJPzJ1A61fEwDBrowBJNN5t1bMQI6bG75un1ZP7k=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9hbXJ5LW5hdnktYnJhbmQtaGVhZGVyLTIuanBn" alt="The Army and Navy Style Guides" loading="lazy"/><p>For decades, companies have realized how important a well executed corporate identity can be to a company’s success. An iconic logo, carefully chosen colors and typography that are thoughtfully and strategically woven into a visual system can help a company express intangible corporate values and reflect the philosophy of a business. </p><p>Depending upon the size of an organization, a company’s brand may need complex rules for how it appears in print, on the web, on packaging, on vehicles, and even how the brand appears in motion. This is where brand guideline documents come in handy. They can be extremely useful for large organizations to communicate the graphic design systems, specifications and rules that the company spent so much money on. </p><p>I absolutely love a good brand style guide. The best ones communicate an easy to grasp philosophy about the ideas behind the designs, and include useful “do’s and don’ts” – examples of the proper use of the rules, and my favorite – what you should NEVER do with their precious logo. They even specify the style and treatment of photography and often the desired tone or vibe of the messaging being communicated. </p><p>Government agencies also picked up on the importance of this type of disciplined brand management for communications with their customers – the public – and have created some fascinating brand style guides for enforcing the rules. </p><h3 id="%E2%80%9Cunmistakably-army%E2%80%9D">“Unmistakably Army”</h3><p>One such government agency that has embraced the power of branding is the U.S. Army. Earlier this year Siegel+Gale, an award-winning branding agency developed <a href="https://www.dezeen.com/2023/04/06/us-army-branding-siegelgale/?ref=beautifulpublicdata.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">updated branding</a> for the Army, including a bold 139 page brand guidelines doc.</p><figure><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Kr-_2wmHZ43Xloospcfp3gTlg0T8wDM10D-V4WmzsMA=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9TY3JlZW5zaG90LTIwMjMtMTAtMDMtYXQtMS4zNi40NC1BTS0yLnBuZw==" alt="The Army and Navy Style Guides" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/uLEWB1d9gc2N14NIV0ER53qGuq08l5GMLknNtM4NdZc=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93NjAwLzIwMjMvMTAvU2NyZWVuc2hvdC0yMDIzLTEwLTAzLWF0LTEuMzYuNDQtQU0tMi5wbmc= 600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Kr-_2wmHZ43Xloospcfp3gTlg0T8wDM10D-V4WmzsMA=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9TY3JlZW5zaG90LTIwMjMtMTAtMDMtYXQtMS4zNi40NC1BTS0yLnBuZw== 878w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" loading="lazy"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/nPAq2gomc5KzbYvEPDmHCkdSmE1u5OlbfsIGKDztOko=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9hcm15LTktMS5wbmc=" alt="The Army and Navy Style Guides" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/IubBki8iG8d6_j8UO45AFkVWTAqJ273eKjDcC9y5cvM=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93NjAwLzIwMjMvMTAvYXJteS05LTEucG5n 600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Ry_NEH_QaXCRNuPp4A6S6lsv8qbu3vKSIS_3x6Ww5xU=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MTAwMC8yMDIzLzEwL2FybXktOS0xLnBuZw== 1000w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/nPAq2gomc5KzbYvEPDmHCkdSmE1u5OlbfsIGKDztOko=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9hcm15LTktMS5wbmc= 1067w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" loading="lazy"/><figcaption><p>Pages from the Army Brand Guidelines. Source: U.S. Army</p></figcaption></figure><p>Before diving into the specific fonts and colors to use, the guidelines set the tone of the brand for the Army with a set of “identity principles”: </p><ul><li>Clear (“Messages should be simple, crisp, and effective”)</li><li>Confident (“It demonstrates belief in positive outcomes and in its unique ability to enact them”) </li><li>Human (“We strive to facilitate easy engagement and illuminate authentic purpose and passion whenever possible”). </li></ul><p>There’s also a note about the brand’s strategy, defining two conceptual &#34;pillars&#34; upon which the brand rests – &#34;Passion &amp; Purpose&#34; and &#34;Community &amp; Connection&#34; (though that is technically four concepts).</p><figure><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/jGrWjcEus-q90gHjwJ13dKTKQSO4Ay9YZfEETWl1Y24=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9TY3JlZW5zaG90LTIwMjMtMTAtMDMtYXQtMS4yMS41Ni1BTS0xLnBuZw==" alt="The Army and Navy Style Guides" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/7ezdR4YhyvkMrnLfaRGyPo-2Bb_Wt0FcXkKQVCXXSAI=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93NjAwLzIwMjMvMTAvU2NyZWVuc2hvdC0yMDIzLTEwLTAzLWF0LTEuMjEuNTYtQU0tMS5wbmc= 600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/vftHtOwy-i_sMivN-vdMYmiCtJHPFej-sVh8NTl6qOs=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MTAwMC8yMDIzLzEwL1NjcmVlbnNob3QtMjAyMy0xMC0wMy1hdC0xLjIxLjU2LUFNLTEucG5n 1000w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Zx6qmYA1zgmQPpqZIWP-WaiwN4J-DZOHIrbz-8EejEI=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MTYwMC8yMDIzLzEwL1NjcmVlbnNob3QtMjAyMy0xMC0wMy1hdC0xLjIxLjU2LUFNLTEucG5n 1600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/detaDzwQxfx01o6C-_57drMstNSRMe2XU1ZSK7gZqIs=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MjQwMC8yMDIzLzEwL1NjcmVlbnNob3QtMjAyMy0xMC0wMy1hdC0xLjIxLjU2LUFNLTEucG5n 2400w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" loading="lazy"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-Ie1H6uV7Q9aLeZm8NZWFjjXkxs0O3n92myMHYRce0c=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9TY3JlZW5zaG90LTIwMjMtMTAtMDMtYXQtMS4xNy41NS1BTS0xLnBuZw==" alt="The Army and Navy Style Guides" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/wwmpY1U_8pdez4NVE9-Ka-N_Xz6C78VGaCczFkfMxrQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93NjAwLzIwMjMvMTAvU2NyZWVuc2hvdC0yMDIzLTEwLTAzLWF0LTEuMTcuNTUtQU0tMS5wbmc= 600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-Ie1H6uV7Q9aLeZm8NZWFjjXkxs0O3n92myMHYRce0c=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9TY3JlZW5zaG90LTIwMjMtMTAtMDMtYXQtMS4xNy41NS1BTS0xLnBuZw== 876w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px" loading="lazy"/><figcaption><p>Left: A page from the Army Brand Guidelines. Right: A page from the Navy Brand Guidelines. Source: U.S. Army, <a href="https://etoolbox.cnrc.navy.mil/assets/documents/BrandGuidelines_Digital.pdf?ref=beautifulpublicdata.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">U.S. Navy</a></p></figcaption></figure><p>The guide lays out a visual language for the fighting force that is utilitarian, hard edged and defined by a primary color palette of four main colors: the iconic dark olive (ARMY GREEN), and three colors that the Army says are inspired by the components of gunpowder: ARMY GOLD for sulfur, WHITE for potassium nitrate and ARMY BLACK for charcoal. A more modern secondary palette evokes desaturated swatches of camouflage, incorporating the pale dusty greens of FIELD 01 and FIELD 02, TAN, rounded out by two shades of cool gray: GRAY 01 and GRAY 02. The way these colors are applied matters, and to help with this, a “color hierarchy” quantifies the primacy of each color and what applications they may be best suited for. </p><figure><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/muYD43lYJQpZ__ythuozqAyWx3MDGYKKAwDSMl5ovAs=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvMjAyMy8xMC9TY3JlZW5zaG90LTIwMjMtMTAtMDItYXQtMTEuMzkuMDQtUE0tMS5wbmc=" alt="The Army and Navy Style Guides" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/kCUNKs44x0yb4N0yTFUW9jh3jpCQzkpE6WLPRF3r_fY=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93NjAwLzIwMjMvMTAvU2NyZWVuc2hvdC0yMDIzLTEwLTAyLWF0LTExLjM5LjA0LVBNLTEucG5n 600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-mc_LfYW5LcDBP8xKDu5ZCfydvhs0mYjNmzBHCWzjNs=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MTAwMC8yMDIzLzEwL1NjcmVlbnNob3QtMjAyMy0xMC0wMi1hdC0xMS4zOS4wNC1QTS0xLnBuZw== 1000w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/qTnZdWdcOZk44x9pnPYbAnLzn1yUaZQ38H_7bT6spqs=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29udGVudC9pbWFnZXMvc2l6ZS93MTYwMC8yMDIzLzEwL1NjcmVlbnNob3QtMjAyMy0xMC0wMi1hdC0xMS4zOS4wNC1QTS0xLnBuZw== 1600w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/DEgMhyGCT5OXR_n_TPRLLLY4KHITUqv06s5c1kGhuiU=/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmVhdXRpZnVscHVibGljZGF0YS5jb20vY29u